TY  - JOUR
AU  - Berg, Tobias
T1  - Playing the Devil's Advocate: The Causal Effect of Risk Management on Loan Quality
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhv040
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 28
IS  - 12
SP  - 3367
EP  - 3406
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This paper studies the dual role of risk managers and loan officers in a bank's organizational structure. Using 75,000 retail mortgage applications, I analyze the effect of risk-management involvement on loan default rates. The bank requires risk-management approval for loans that are considered risky based on hard information, using a sharp threshold that changes during the sample period. Using a regression discontinuity design and a difference-in-differences estimator, I am able to show that risk-management involvement reduces loan default rates by more than 50%. My findings suggest that a two-agent model can help to facilitate efficient screening decisions.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhv040
ER  - 



