TY  - JOUR
AU  - Oehmke, Martin
AU  - Zawadowski, Adam
T1  - Synthetic or Real? The Equilibrium Effects of Credit Default Swaps on Bond Markets
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhv047
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 28
IS  - 12
SP  - 3303
EP  - 3337
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We provide a model of nonredundant credit default swaps (CDSs), building on the observation that CDSs have lower trading costs than bonds. CDS introduction involves a trade-off: it crowds out existing demand for the bond, but improves the bond allocation by allowing long-term investors to become levered basis traders and absorb more of the bond supply. We characterize conditions under which CDS introduction raises bond prices. The model predicts a negative CDS-bond basis, as well as turnover and price impact patterns that are consistent with empirical evidence. We also show that a ban on naked CDSs can raise borrowing costs.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhv047
ER  - 



